description: A circular route through the beautiful Marston Vale in Befordshire. The walk passes Ampthill Park, Jackdaw Hill, Marston Mortaine and Stewartby Lake Country Park. The walk also visits the Engligh Heritage owned ruined house at Houghton, which is free to visit and commands excellent views of the surrounding area.
